cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.HC 

The paper focuses on skeleton-based gesture recognition, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a new classification model that involves a temporal transformer module, which is a learning-based module, indicating that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also proposes a new feature descriptor, path signature, which is a mathematical tool, indicating that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper tests its method on three benchmark gesture datasets, indicating that it may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper emphasizes the significance of fine hand movements in the gesture, indicating that it may also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
